gomodel:SYNGO_3789  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figures 3A,B,D,E: Presynaptically, the highest density of syntaxin-1 immunoreactivity in the presynaptic compartment was located at the plasma membrane of the AZ. Many gold particles were also observed attached to presynaptic vesicles.\nFigure 5 shows quantification of immune-gold particles at presynapse.\n\n19/6/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: M&M: Electron micrographs from RATS (n = 3) were obtained from asymmetric synapses (Schaffer collateral synapses) from the middle layer of stratum radiatum of the CA1 region of the hippocampus." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
